    <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
      <head>Historical Information
</head>
      <p>Louisa County was named for Louisa, a daughter of George II.  It was formed from Hanover County in 1742.  Its area is 514 square miles, and the county seat is Louisa.   
</p>
      
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>Louisa County (Va.) Bonds/Comissions/Oaths, 1767-1924 circa, undated, typically consist of bonds, commissions, oaths, certificates, and appointments related to holding public office. Some collections can include ministers' bonds. 
</p>
    </scopecontent>
